1
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:28,666
Did this sword commit murder?

2
00:00:28,750 --> 00:00:30,083
What?

3
00:00:30,166 --> 00:00:32,541
[MARO] If asking if the sword
magically walked in here

4
00:00:32,625 --> 00:00:35,791
of its own volition and
killed the imperial envoy.

5
00:00:35,875 --> 00:00:38,333
When searching for one
single grain of sand,

6
00:00:38,416 --> 00:00:40,791
a wise man will choose
to run the entire beach

7
00:00:40,875 --> 00:00:42,833
through a sieve. Understand?

8
00:00:42,916 --> 00:00:45,708
[MASAMUNE] You sure know how
to attract attention, Kiku.

9
00:00:45,791 --> 00:00:48,166
Let's go...
they'll be coming soon.

10
00:00:48,250 --> 00:00:49,666
I know it's
a lot to ask,

11
00:00:49,750 --> 00:00:52,000
but do you think it would be
alright if I came with you?

12
00:00:52,083 --> 00:00:54,208
I suppose
you'll have to.

13
00:00:54,291 --> 00:00:56,250
[KIKUCHIYO] But he'll
change his mind soon enough.

14
00:00:56,333 --> 00:00:58,000
I'll bring up the rear!

15
00:00:59,208 --> 00:01:01,125
[GOROBEI]
Forget them! Come on!

16
00:01:01,208 --> 00:01:02,958
Kikuchiyo!

17
00:01:03,041 --> 00:01:04,666
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS]

18
00:01:04,750 --> 00:01:06,791
[KIKUCHIYO]
You better not screw this up!

19
00:01:06,875 --> 00:01:09,000
Save those farmers, okay!

20
00:01:19,041 --> 00:01:24,041
♪ opening song ♪

21
00:03:00,375 --> 00:03:02,041
[YOHEI] What is a
Nobuseri doing here?

22
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:04,083
They're attacking!

23
00:03:20,208 --> 00:03:22,583
I think they were just
checkin' on the harvest.

24
00:03:22,666 --> 00:03:24,375
The rice is
about to bend.

25
00:03:24,458 --> 00:03:27,125
And still no samurai yet.

26
00:03:38,958 --> 00:03:41,125
They're gone.

27
00:03:41,208 --> 00:03:43,125
Anyone got any
brilliant plans?

28
00:03:43,208 --> 00:03:45,875
We could fight
our way out, sensei.

29
00:03:46,875 --> 00:03:49,416
But we can't wage war
on empty stomachs can we?

30
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:51,541
We were in such a hurry
when we fled the city... 

31
00:03:51,625 --> 00:03:53,208
I left the rice behind...

32
00:03:53,291 --> 00:03:54,125
I'm sorry.

33
00:03:54,208 --> 00:03:55,541
Oh, that's not
what I meant...

34
00:03:55,625 --> 00:03:58,583
It's time we call on old allies,
and lay low for a while.

35
00:03:58,666 --> 00:04:00,541
[GOROBEI] Got someone
special in mind?

36
00:04:00,625 --> 00:04:02,916
The only one I'd trust
is my former mate.

37
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,250
You mean you
were married Sensei?

38
00:04:05,333 --> 00:04:08,666
Of course I'm not sure
if that's still an option.

39
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:11,750
We'll leave here at sunset...

40
00:04:11,833 --> 00:04:13,958
Everyone rest up until then.

41
00:04:22,708 --> 00:04:25,583
[PROSTITUTE] Wanna have
some fun tonight, big man?

42
00:04:25,666 --> 00:04:27,208
[MISTER]
Maybe next time, honey.

43
00:04:28,333 --> 00:04:30,125
[FIREFLY CHORUS]
♪ Leave grief at the door, ♪

44
00:04:30,208 --> 00:04:32,416
♪ Sit back and let us pour... ♪

45
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:34,458
♪ Have a drink then
have one more, ♪

46
00:04:34,541 --> 00:04:36,791
♪ 'Cause that's
what sake's for... ♪

47
00:04:36,875 --> 00:04:38,750
♪ Too much pain in life, ♪

48
00:04:38,833 --> 00:04:41,083
♪ So lose the
sword and knife... ♪

49
00:04:41,166 --> 00:04:43,125
♪ Dance your stress away, ♪

50
00:04:43,208 --> 00:04:45,375
♪ If only for today... ♪

51
00:04:45,458 --> 00:04:47,458
♪ Forget your cares,
forget your strife, ♪

52
00:04:47,541 --> 00:04:49,875
♪ An' tonight
forget your wife... ♪

53
00:04:49,958 --> 00:04:50,958
♪ Eat it up... ♪

54
00:04:51,041 --> 00:04:51,958
♪ Drink it down... ♪

55
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:54,416
♪ At Firefly House! ♪

56
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:55,875
[CHEERING]

57
00:04:55,958 --> 00:04:58,125
[MERCHANT]
All right, now it's my turn!

58
00:04:58,208 --> 00:05:01,958
[SHAMISEN MUSIC]

59
00:05:02,041 --> 00:05:03,791
[FIREFLY CHORUS]
♪ Leave grief at the door, ♪

60
00:05:03,875 --> 00:05:06,208
♪ Sit back and let us pour... ♪

61
00:05:06,291 --> 00:05:08,083
♪ Have a drink then 
have one more, ♪

62
00:05:08,166 --> 00:05:10,541
♪ 'Cause that's
what sake's for... ♪

63
00:05:10,625 --> 00:05:13,375
♪ Too much pain in life... ♪

64
00:05:13,458 --> 00:05:16,250
[RONIN SAMURAI]
Lousy merchants...

65
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:18,708
How 'bout a refill?

66
00:05:18,791 --> 00:05:20,958
[OLD LADY]
How 'bout you pay first?

67
00:05:21,916 --> 00:05:23,750
No money, no sake.

68
00:05:23,833 --> 00:05:24,791
[FIREFLY CHORUS]
♪ So eat it up... ♪

69
00:05:24,875 --> 00:05:25,708
♪ Drink it down... ♪

70
00:05:25,791 --> 00:05:28,333
♪ At the Firefly House! ♪

71
00:05:28,416 --> 00:05:29,708
[CHEERING IN BACKGROUND]

72
00:05:29,791 --> 00:05:33,583
[RONIN SAMURAI
GRUNTS ANGRILY]

73
00:05:37,375 --> 00:05:38,541
[SHICHIROJI]
Whoa there...

74
00:05:38,625 --> 00:05:40,666
Please, allow me to
carry this for you.

75
00:05:40,750 --> 00:05:42,708
Thanks, Shichiroji,
you're too kind.

76
00:05:42,791 --> 00:05:44,791
Oh please,
it's nothin'.

77
00:05:53,708 --> 00:05:55,625
Ah... That hits the spot!

78
00:05:55,708 --> 00:05:57,708
[YUKINO] Honey?

79
00:05:57,791 --> 00:05:59,041
Oh, Yukino!

80
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:00,916
I thought you were
on call tonight.

81
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,416
[YUKINO]
Drinking leftovers again?

82
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:04,583
You know you can have your own.

83
00:06:04,666 --> 00:06:05,958
Y'know,
old habits and all--

84
00:06:06,041 --> 00:06:08,375
I hate to see
things go to waste.

85
00:06:13,083 --> 00:06:16,208
Mmm... That is good...! <i>Anago</i> ?

86
00:06:16,291 --> 00:06:18,333
[YUKINO] Yes, we got
some nice conger eels

87
00:06:18,416 --> 00:06:20,000
from the Seiso Trench.

88
00:06:20,083 --> 00:06:24,250
Mm-Mmm! I've died
and gone to heaven.

89
00:06:26,208 --> 00:06:29,125
The fireflies are dancing
all around you tonight...

90
00:06:29,208 --> 00:06:31,583
They like you.

91
00:06:31,666 --> 00:06:32,541
[CRASHING SOUND]

92
00:06:32,625 --> 00:06:34,458
[WOMAN SCREAMS]

93
00:06:36,125 --> 00:06:37,625
Please don't
do anything rash.

94
00:06:37,708 --> 00:06:40,333
Come on... It's me.

95
00:06:43,541 --> 00:06:44,875
[YUKINO SIGHS]

96
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:50,416
[MERCHANT]
If it's money you want,

97
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:51,791
I've got more than
I know what to do with!

98
00:06:51,875 --> 00:06:53,666
I don't want your filthy coins!

99
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:54,958
Ahh...!

100
00:06:55,041 --> 00:06:56,250
Great Samurai, please
put away your sword--

101
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:57,333
we can talk
this through.

102
00:06:57,416 --> 00:06:59,291
You're not fit to
address me, wench!

103
00:06:59,375 --> 00:07:01,791
When Lord Shingen invaded
the fortress of Rock-Face, 

104
00:07:01,875 --> 00:07:05,791
I distinguished myself
as his third spear man!

105
00:07:05,875 --> 00:07:07,666
That was before
you merchants came...

106
00:07:07,750 --> 00:07:10,166
reducing heroes to beggars!

107
00:07:10,250 --> 00:07:11,708
Ahh! Huh...?!

108
00:07:11,791 --> 00:07:14,250
Now, now, you won't
be needing this in here.

109
00:07:14,333 --> 00:07:17,416
If you don't get outta
my way I'll cut you down!

110
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:20,208
[SHICHIROJI]
Tempting offer. But no thanks.

111
00:07:20,291 --> 00:07:22,833
[RONIN SAMURAI GRUNTS]

112
00:07:22,916 --> 00:07:24,708
[RONIN SAMURAI YELLS]

113
00:07:24,791 --> 00:07:27,000
You'll pay for that!

114
00:07:28,208 --> 00:07:31,583
[RONIN SAMURAI YELLS]

115
00:07:37,166 --> 00:07:40,041
This town's a sanctuary...
The Village of Respite...

116
00:07:40,125 --> 00:07:42,541
You should raise your cup,
not your sword... 

117
00:07:42,625 --> 00:07:44,750
So how about it?
My treat of course.

118
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:47,333
You have no idea what
it means to be a samurai.

119
00:07:47,416 --> 00:07:49,958
You know the whole Samurai thing
went out of style years ago--

120
00:07:50,041 --> 00:07:51,125
why don't you give it a rest?

121
00:07:51,208 --> 00:07:53,333
I think you'd be a great dancer.

122
00:07:53,416 --> 00:07:55,791
A samurai is
never anything else!

123
00:07:55,875 --> 00:07:57,208
[RONIN SAMURAI YELLS]

124
00:08:06,458 --> 00:08:07,333
[RONIN SAMURAI YELLS]

125
00:08:07,416 --> 00:08:08,458
[SHICHIROJI]
Thanks for coming,

126
00:08:08,541 --> 00:08:11,083
and do watch your
step on the way out!

127
00:08:11,166 --> 00:08:13,333
Uh... Ah... Ah...

128
00:08:13,416 --> 00:08:15,416
[RONIN SAMURAI YELLS]

129
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:16,375
[CROWD LAUGHS]

130
00:08:16,458 --> 00:08:18,458
You've... shamed me...

131
00:08:18,541 --> 00:08:19,583
[SHICHIROJI]
Haven't you heard?

132
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:20,958
They're hunting samurai.

133
00:08:21,041 --> 00:08:22,125
You're gonna have
trouble fitting in

134
00:08:22,208 --> 00:08:23,833
here or in Kougakyo...

135
00:08:23,916 --> 00:08:28,041
...unless you're ready to
renounce your warrior ways.

136
00:08:28,125 --> 00:08:30,458
You'll regret this!

137
00:08:32,708 --> 00:08:35,958
Aww! Hey wait!
The bill...! Ah!

138
00:08:36,041 --> 00:08:38,208
[SHICHIROJI YELLS]

139
00:08:41,291 --> 00:08:43,875
[KIRARA]
It's so beautiful.

140
00:08:43,958 --> 00:08:46,166
But what does everybody
do down there?

141
00:08:46,250 --> 00:08:48,041
Well they... uhm...

142
00:08:48,125 --> 00:08:50,333
They purge all the pent-up
stress from their bodies

143
00:08:50,416 --> 00:08:53,291
and cleanse their minds of
life's trials and tribulations.

144
00:08:53,375 --> 00:08:55,625
[KATSUSHIRO] So it's like
a wash-house for the soul?

145
00:08:55,708 --> 00:08:57,125
I didn't know they had those.

146
00:08:57,208 --> 00:09:01,166
Your social status doesn't
mean anything past those walls.

147
00:09:01,250 --> 00:09:03,000
And neither does
the magistrate's power--

148
00:09:03,083 --> 00:09:04,333
it's a little pocket of freedom.

149
00:09:04,416 --> 00:09:06,250
Well that's what
they say, anyway.

150
00:09:06,333 --> 00:09:08,750
Now, what about
Kikuchiyo-dono?

151
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:11,083
[KATSUSHIRO] You've been
thinking about him, too?

152
00:09:11,166 --> 00:09:14,208
Relax--not even hell would be
dumb enough to take him in.

153
00:09:14,291 --> 00:09:16,708
I doubt we've seen
the last of him.

154
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,750
[WHISTLING SOUND]

155
00:09:20,833 --> 00:09:23,083
[KIKUCHIYO] Okay, I'm getting
really tired of this, guys.

156
00:09:23,166 --> 00:09:27,208
But if you don't want
your lives, I'll take 'em!

157
00:09:29,916 --> 00:09:31,541
Aw, c'mon...!

158
00:09:31,625 --> 00:09:35,125
This only works if you come
running at me, you stupid goats!

159
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:45,750
[YUKINO]
Hm...

160
00:09:45,833 --> 00:09:48,666
I thought you weren't
going to do anything rash.

161
00:09:48,750 --> 00:09:51,375
Yeah, that's the
problem with pride...

162
00:09:51,458 --> 00:09:53,291
[YUKINO]
You or that drunk samurai?

163
00:09:53,375 --> 00:09:55,791
These days, a samurai's
only options are either

164
00:09:55,875 --> 00:09:59,208
find work as a bodyguard or
join up with the Nobuseri.

165
00:09:59,291 --> 00:10:01,875
You're neither of those
things and you're a samurai.

166
00:10:01,958 --> 00:10:03,375
I gave that up.

167
00:10:03,458 --> 00:10:06,666
You're a terrible liar,
I know what makes you happy.

168
00:10:06,750 --> 00:10:09,333
You know how when fireflies
are just young little glowworms,

169
00:10:09,416 --> 00:10:10,708
they flit about in the water,

170
00:10:10,791 --> 00:10:12,666
stirring up bubbles
and making noise?

171
00:10:12,750 --> 00:10:16,166
Yes, feasting on snails
and slugs and other things.

172
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:19,000
Yet when they're grown they
settle, and become silent.

173
00:10:19,083 --> 00:10:20,500
My splashing days are over.

174
00:10:20,583 --> 00:10:22,708
I'll be right here for
the rest of my life...

175
00:10:22,791 --> 00:10:25,708
Because I owe this life to you.

176
00:10:25,791 --> 00:10:29,333
Knock it off...
Or I might believe you.

177
00:10:30,375 --> 00:10:32,000
Is something wrong?

178
00:10:34,666 --> 00:10:37,708
It's good to find you alive...
Shichiroji-san.

179
00:10:37,791 --> 00:10:39,708
As I live and breathe...

180
00:10:39,791 --> 00:10:41,583
[KAMBEI]
We need shelter for the night.

181
00:10:41,666 --> 00:10:43,416
Well of course you do!

182
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:45,125
[KAMBEI]
Sorry for the imposition...

183
00:10:45,208 --> 00:10:46,541
C'mon!

184
00:10:49,333 --> 00:10:50,583
[KIRARA]
We thank you.

185
00:10:50,666 --> 00:10:51,708
[WHISTLING SOUND]

186
00:10:51,791 --> 00:10:54,541
[KOMACHI]
Oh, I don't like that noise.

187
00:10:56,375 --> 00:10:59,708
[WHISTLING SOUND]

188
00:11:00,958 --> 00:11:02,250
A sea imp?

189
00:11:02,333 --> 00:11:03,375
Ahh!

190
00:11:03,458 --> 00:11:07,041
[KIKUCHIYO]
I'm no imp! I'm a samurai!

191
00:11:14,875 --> 00:11:16,416
[KYUZO]
Don't help.

192
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,166
A machine samurai
has been spotted,

193
00:11:25,250 --> 00:11:26,583
in the Village of Respite.

194
00:11:26,666 --> 00:11:29,083
[UKYO]
Mm-Hmm...

195
00:11:29,166 --> 00:11:31,791
Then what are we waiting for?

196
00:11:58,708 --> 00:12:02,000
I'd like you all to meet
my old mate, Shichiroji.

197
00:12:04,875 --> 00:12:06,375
Lady Shichiroji...

198
00:12:06,458 --> 00:12:07,333
[KAMBEI COUGHS]

199
00:12:07,416 --> 00:12:09,208
Katsushiro, this guy.

200
00:12:09,291 --> 00:12:11,250
Ah... Oh...

201
00:12:11,333 --> 00:12:12,458
Mm-Hmm...

202
00:12:12,541 --> 00:12:13,791
You goof...

203
00:12:13,875 --> 00:12:15,583
You thought he meant
"mate" in the literal sense?

204
00:12:15,666 --> 00:12:17,166
[KAMBEI]
Heh, heh, heh...

205
00:12:17,250 --> 00:12:20,833
He and I shared the thrills and
sorrows of war for many years.

206
00:12:20,916 --> 00:12:22,416
Oh, I get it.

207
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:23,958
So the young
lady is...?

208
00:12:24,041 --> 00:12:25,833
[YUKINO]
I'm Yukino.

209
00:12:25,916 --> 00:12:27,833
Shichiroji-dono,
you lucky dog...

210
00:12:27,916 --> 00:12:29,666
to have such
a beautiful wife!

211
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:32,541
Oh no, not quite...
Roji and I aren't married.

212
00:12:32,625 --> 00:12:34,625
I'd love to hear the
story of how you two met.

213
00:12:34,708 --> 00:12:35,750
[YUKINO]
Oh, it was nothing.

214
00:12:35,833 --> 00:12:37,500
I just... fished him
out of the river.

215
00:12:37,583 --> 00:12:39,458
So he used
to be a fish?

216
00:12:39,541 --> 00:12:42,291
It'll have been...
five years soon.

217
00:12:48,541 --> 00:12:51,291
Hey! Just like Momotaro
in that old fairy tale.

218
00:12:51,375 --> 00:12:53,125
I guess you're right...

219
00:12:53,208 --> 00:12:54,875
The little baby
inside of a peach,

220
00:12:54,958 --> 00:12:56,875
floating down the river...

221
00:12:56,958 --> 00:13:00,500
[LAUGHING]

222
00:13:00,583 --> 00:13:02,666
So you've got
Ayamaro after you.

223
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:05,666
Yeah, for some reason that
guy's really got it in for us.

224
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:07,666
I heard that an
envoy was murdered.

225
00:13:07,750 --> 00:13:09,916
Convenient excuse
for a samurai hunt.

226
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,916
They've been
looking for one.

227
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,875
Suppose the Magistrate's
men were to come here,

228
00:13:13,958 --> 00:13:16,375
to Firefly House--how long
could we hold them off?

229
00:13:16,458 --> 00:13:18,583
Not long if even at all...

230
00:13:18,666 --> 00:13:20,875
But there is a
secret escape route.

231
00:13:20,958 --> 00:13:24,500
Will it take us outside
of Kougakyo's boundaries?

232
00:13:24,583 --> 00:13:25,750
If you can make it past

233
00:13:25,833 --> 00:13:28,041
the lair of the
Shikimoribito--the Guardians.

234
00:13:28,125 --> 00:13:30,708
Why, has that been a problem
for people in the past?

235
00:13:30,791 --> 00:13:34,083
Not sure... No one's ever
made it back to let me know.

236
00:13:38,833 --> 00:13:41,333
That's enough scary
talk for one evening.

237
00:13:42,958 --> 00:13:44,833
I want you all to
have a full taste of

238
00:13:44,916 --> 00:13:47,833
the Firefly House experience.

239
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:57,583
[HEIHACHI]
Now this is what I call luxury!

240
00:14:04,458 --> 00:14:05,666
Oh, man...!

241
00:14:05,750 --> 00:14:07,833
The rice is great!
It's from Omachi?

242
00:14:07,916 --> 00:14:09,333
Yes, how
can you tell?

243
00:14:09,416 --> 00:14:10,833
I'm better with a
pair of chopsticks

244
00:14:10,916 --> 00:14:12,666
than I am with a sword.

245
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:17,041
Would you mind
passing this around?

246
00:14:19,208 --> 00:14:21,458
Are you all right Katsushiro,
your face is turning red.

247
00:14:21,541 --> 00:14:22,750
Oh it is?

248
00:14:22,833 --> 00:14:24,791
I guess it's just
a little bit warm in here...

249
00:14:24,875 --> 00:14:27,791
[YUKINO]
Really? Have some air.

250
00:14:29,250 --> 00:14:31,000
[KOMACHI]
I think he's allergic to girls.

251
00:14:31,083 --> 00:14:32,375
[GROUP LAUGHS]

252
00:14:32,458 --> 00:14:35,041
You all seem like
one big happy family.

253
00:14:35,125 --> 00:14:36,833
Those three over there
came to the city looking to

254
00:14:36,916 --> 00:14:39,291
recruit samurai to protect
their village from the Bandits,

255
00:14:39,375 --> 00:14:40,958
and one by one
we came together.

256
00:14:41,041 --> 00:14:43,875
They won us over
with their pure spirit.

257
00:14:43,958 --> 00:14:47,125
So a few leftovers are gonna
wage war on the Nobuseri, huh?

258
00:14:47,208 --> 00:14:49,625
If that's what it
takes, then yes.

259
00:14:52,625 --> 00:14:57,583
[MURMURING]

260
00:15:10,666 --> 00:15:14,541
War with the Nobuseri--
but that sounds... dangerous.

261
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:19,708
Aren't you gonna eat anything
sis--it's really good!

262
00:15:19,791 --> 00:15:21,666
[KIRARA] It wouldn't be right
to feast like an empress,

263
00:15:21,750 --> 00:15:23,750
while the rest of
the village is starving.

264
00:15:23,833 --> 00:15:26,166
Ah... don't be so hard
on yourself, you've earned this!

265
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:27,833
Back in the village we
usually don't even have

266
00:15:27,916 --> 00:15:31,541
a whole fish to share between
us but maybe once a year.

267
00:15:33,208 --> 00:15:34,750
[RIKICHI SIGHS]

268
00:15:34,833 --> 00:15:36,375
Everyone's life is
full of suffering,

269
00:15:36,458 --> 00:15:38,250
but going hungry
won't make it better...

270
00:15:38,333 --> 00:15:41,416
Bodies don't last long
on a diet of virtue alone.

271
00:15:42,958 --> 00:15:44,666
Please forgive my rudeness.

272
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:45,833
Uh, Honey...

273
00:15:45,916 --> 00:15:49,125
Uh, how 'bout some
music to help us digest?

274
00:15:51,291 --> 00:15:56,291
[SHAMISEN MUSIC]

275
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:01,291
[HEIHACHI]
Wow! I love this place!

276
00:16:01,375 --> 00:16:06,708
[GOROBEI]
Heh... Apparently so.

277
00:16:06,791 --> 00:16:09,166
Here, let me pour you some sake?

278
00:16:09,250 --> 00:16:10,833
I don't feel
like drinking.

279
00:16:10,916 --> 00:16:13,625
I know you're worried about
the rest of your village.

280
00:16:13,708 --> 00:16:15,041
[KIRARA SIGHS]

281
00:16:20,708 --> 00:16:22,875
[OLD LADY YAWNS]

282
00:16:22,958 --> 00:16:24,208
[KIKUCHIYO]
Hey, as long as you're bored,

283
00:16:24,291 --> 00:16:27,083
why don't you take
a look at my family tree? Heh...

284
00:16:27,166 --> 00:16:29,541
Now then...
which one am I again?

285
00:16:29,625 --> 00:16:32,000
Huh? Don't ask me.

286
00:16:32,083 --> 00:16:35,791
[KNOCKING]

287
00:16:35,875 --> 00:16:36,666
[TESSAI]
Open up!

288
00:16:36,750 --> 00:16:38,625
[HORN HONKS]

289
00:16:38,708 --> 00:16:39,750
[ROBOTIC VOICE]
Curfew has passed,

290
00:16:39,833 --> 00:16:41,958
and the Village of
Respite is closed.

291
00:16:42,041 --> 00:16:43,458
Please come back
in the morning.

292
00:16:43,541 --> 00:16:46,416
After closing, not even the
lord of the manor may enter.

293
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:50,250
[UKYO] Well, diplomacy won't
work. Let's find another way.

294
00:16:55,541 --> 00:16:57,166
[ROBOTIC VOICE]
No exceptions will be made...

295
00:16:57,250 --> 00:17:00,750
[DISTORTED ROBOTIC VOICE]
No... ex... cep... tions...

296
00:17:09,458 --> 00:17:12,125
[SHICHIROJI]
I'm surprised you knew...

297
00:17:12,208 --> 00:17:14,208
That I was
still alive, I mean.

298
00:17:14,291 --> 00:17:16,333
You've given up
the samurai life.

299
00:17:16,416 --> 00:17:19,375
Yeah... Back in that moat,
I recalled my first life...

300
00:17:19,458 --> 00:17:22,166
that of a
humble vendor...

301
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:23,958
Then the dark
of night fell...

302
00:17:24,041 --> 00:17:25,625
And the second
ship burned down...

303
00:17:25,708 --> 00:17:27,416
As it came crashing
down around my body,

304
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:30,000
I truly thought
it would be my end.

305
00:17:30,083 --> 00:17:31,958
Have you grown tired of battle?

306
00:17:32,041 --> 00:17:33,250
"Battle"?

307
00:17:33,333 --> 00:17:35,916
Now there's a
nostalgic word for us.

308
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:38,333
[KAMBEI] Times have certainly
changed, haven't they?

309
00:17:38,416 --> 00:17:40,125
It used to be that
one would train hard

310
00:17:40,208 --> 00:17:42,250
in order to go off to war,

311
00:17:42,333 --> 00:17:46,666
to achieve glory, to eventually
become daimyo of his own land...

312
00:17:46,750 --> 00:17:49,125
That is all any of
us ever dreamed of.

313
00:17:49,208 --> 00:17:50,250
[SHICHIROJI]
Nowadays, those dreams can't be

314
00:17:50,333 --> 00:17:52,125
won by sword or spear...

315
00:17:52,208 --> 00:17:53,541
they're won by
the highest bid.

316
00:17:53,625 --> 00:17:55,041
[KAMBEI]
Exactly.

317
00:17:55,125 --> 00:17:56,583
[SHAMISEN MUSIC]

318
00:17:56,666 --> 00:18:03,958
♪ I once cut down bandits
from all three thousand lands. ♪

319
00:18:04,041 --> 00:18:06,791
♪ Cut them down
and got cut down. ♪

320
00:18:06,875 --> 00:18:12,041
♪ But still... 
But still I stand. ♪

321
00:18:14,791 --> 00:18:16,541
I'll be at
your side.

322
00:18:16,625 --> 00:18:18,958
There's no reward or fame.
Only a bloody war.

323
00:18:19,041 --> 00:18:20,125
Are you sure?

324
00:18:20,208 --> 00:18:21,791
Yes.

325
00:18:21,875 --> 00:18:25,000
This time we may
meet our deaths.

326
00:18:26,875 --> 00:18:29,333
[KIKUCHIYO SNORES]

327
00:18:35,125 --> 00:18:36,708
[YUKINO]
Ah, to be young again.

328
00:18:36,791 --> 00:18:38,250
You have such beautiful skin.

329
00:18:38,333 --> 00:18:41,125
Too bad... it's always
covered with dirt and sweat.

330
00:18:41,208 --> 00:18:42,375
[YUKINO]
Not tonight...

331
00:18:42,458 --> 00:18:44,500
After we finish bathing,
I'll do your makeup.

332
00:18:44,583 --> 00:18:47,166
[KIRARA] Oh no, I'm sorry,
I can't wear makeup.

333
00:18:47,250 --> 00:18:48,541
[YUKINO]
You're so guarded...

334
00:18:48,625 --> 00:18:51,500
This is where you come
to forget earthly concerns.

335
00:18:52,750 --> 00:18:54,708
So that young samurai...

336
00:18:54,791 --> 00:18:56,458
[KIRARA]
You mean Katsushiro?

337
00:18:56,541 --> 00:18:58,416
[YUKINO]
He is awfully cute...

338
00:18:58,500 --> 00:19:00,375
[KIRARA]
I really hadn't noticed.

339
00:19:00,458 --> 00:19:02,500
[YUKINO]
I can tell he fancies you.

340
00:19:02,583 --> 00:19:06,500
[KIRARA] I'm just not
interested in men right now.

341
00:19:06,583 --> 00:19:09,000
But seeing the way that you
and Shichiroji are together

342
00:19:09,083 --> 00:19:11,166
kind of gives me
hope for the future.

343
00:19:11,250 --> 00:19:14,000
Oh, thank you.

344
00:19:14,083 --> 00:19:15,500
But in the fairy-tale...

345
00:19:15,583 --> 00:19:18,791
Momotaro always leaves
to slay the demons.

346
00:19:18,875 --> 00:19:21,583
[CLATTERING SOUND]

347
00:19:21,666 --> 00:19:22,833
[YUKINO GASPS]

348
00:19:22,916 --> 00:19:24,958
They found you.

349
00:19:25,041 --> 00:19:26,458
[KIRARA GASPS]

350
00:19:30,666 --> 00:19:33,916
You're sure this is where
that machine samurai went?

351
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,125
[WITNESS YELLS]

352
00:19:35,208 --> 00:19:37,000
You think my Kirara
is in there with him?

353
00:19:40,791 --> 00:19:42,125
[YUKINO]
The hunters are outside!

354
00:19:42,208 --> 00:19:43,375
[GOROBEI]
You're kidding me!

355
00:19:43,458 --> 00:19:44,958
How'd they know
where we are?

356
00:19:45,041 --> 00:19:47,083
I'm sure no one
saw us get here...

357
00:19:47,166 --> 00:19:48,625
[KAMBEI] That's
the way war goes.

358
00:19:48,708 --> 00:19:50,958
Get everybody else up!

359
00:19:51,041 --> 00:19:52,166
[SHICHIROJI]
Under these floorboards,

360
00:19:52,250 --> 00:19:53,666
there's a canal that'll
get us out of here.

361
00:19:53,750 --> 00:19:55,125
We can take my boat.

362
00:19:55,208 --> 00:19:56,333
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS]

363
00:19:56,416 --> 00:19:57,708
[KIKUCHIYO]
Hey, get your hands off of me!

364
00:19:57,791 --> 00:19:59,166
[GUARD 2] We're samurai hunters.
Please come quietly.

365
00:19:59,250 --> 00:20:00,625
[KIKUCHIYO]
Oh, it's you guys. Hey!

366
00:20:00,708 --> 00:20:02,333
Wanna check out my family tree?

367
00:20:02,416 --> 00:20:04,375
Ah! Kiku?!

368
00:20:04,458 --> 00:20:06,666
[HEIHACHI] That moron
led 'em right to us!

369
00:20:06,750 --> 00:20:09,958
[GOROBEI] I swear,
he's a curse on us all!

370
00:20:10,041 --> 00:20:12,000
[HEIHACHI]
D'oh! Here he comes!

371
00:20:12,916 --> 00:20:15,083
[THUD]

372
00:20:15,166 --> 00:20:16,583
[KAMBEI]
You're late.

373
00:20:16,666 --> 00:20:19,041
[KIKUCHIYO] Hey, I've been
looking all over for you guys!

374
00:20:19,125 --> 00:20:20,500
Why are you all frowning?

375
00:20:20,583 --> 00:20:22,875
Well, whatever it is, rest
assured, now that I'm back,

376
00:20:22,958 --> 00:20:25,083
everything will be all right!

377
00:20:25,166 --> 00:20:27,166
Everything will be all right!

378
00:20:27,250 --> 00:20:28,958
[UKYO] Kirara!
Oh, I've found you!

379
00:20:29,041 --> 00:20:31,833
Delicate flowers don't
belong in a place like this...

380
00:20:31,916 --> 00:20:33,708
Let me take you away from here.

381
00:20:33,791 --> 00:20:35,541
[KIKUCHIYO] All right,
you asked for it!

382
00:20:35,625 --> 00:20:37,250
I'm gonna smash you flat!

383
00:20:37,333 --> 00:20:38,958
[SHICHIROJI] Hold on, this
is the Village of Respite,

384
00:20:39,041 --> 00:20:40,500
where the use of
swords is forbidden. 

385
00:20:40,583 --> 00:20:42,666
I can't have you
breaking the rules...

386
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:45,000
[HYOGO] Shall I break
your kneecaps instead?

387
00:20:45,083 --> 00:20:47,166
[GOROBEI] Didn't you hear the
man? This is a sword-free zone!

388
00:20:47,250 --> 00:20:48,875
[HYOGO]
Enough excuses!

389
00:20:54,541 --> 00:20:57,208
Secret Technique:
Floor Mat Fortress!

390
00:21:03,583 --> 00:21:05,041
All right now follow
me down below...

391
00:21:05,125 --> 00:21:07,916
Feels like old times
already, huh Kambei-sama?

392
00:21:10,083 --> 00:21:12,458
[TESSAI] When I give the
signal, we all attack at once!

393
00:21:12,541 --> 00:21:13,875
[UKYO]
I can't let you do that!

394
00:21:13,958 --> 00:21:15,208
What if one of
these clumsy brutes

395
00:21:15,291 --> 00:21:17,458
gets a scratch on my
Kirara's perfect face?!

396
00:21:17,541 --> 00:21:18,666
Please...

397
00:21:18,750 --> 00:21:20,291
Have some faith in our
skills Young Master.

398
00:21:20,375 --> 00:21:22,250
Why should I?

399
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:25,458
Honestly Tessai, sometimes
I don't know where your head is.

400
00:21:25,541 --> 00:21:27,458
[TESSAI YELLS]

401
00:21:27,541 --> 00:21:30,208
Ah! Tessai,
what have you done?!

402
00:21:31,958 --> 00:21:33,458
[YUKINO]
So you're really leaving.

403
00:21:33,541 --> 00:21:34,750
[SHICHIROJI]
I'm sorry.

404
00:21:34,833 --> 00:21:36,750
I knew you weren't through
being a samurai yet.

405
00:21:36,833 --> 00:21:39,375
I hope this doesn't hurt
Firefly House too badly.

406
00:21:39,458 --> 00:21:42,625
Don't worry, I can
handle a little trouble.

407
00:21:43,583 --> 00:21:45,500
[KIKUCHIYO] I hate to break up
this gut wrenching farewell,

408
00:21:45,583 --> 00:21:46,791
but the bad guys are comin'.

409
00:21:46,875 --> 00:21:48,750
So if you're with us, let's go!

410
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:50,083
[KOMACHI]
Knock it off, Kiku!

411
00:21:50,166 --> 00:21:52,375
Don't forget this.

412
00:21:52,458 --> 00:21:53,833
Thanks.

413
00:22:03,416 --> 00:22:07,375
I hope... I hope the
Nobuseri get you...

414
00:22:12,541 --> 00:22:13,791
[KIRARA]
Lady Yukino!

415
00:22:13,875 --> 00:22:16,458
Remember--Momotaro always
comes back in the end, 

416
00:22:16,541 --> 00:22:19,916
with a mountain of
treasure! No matter what.

417
00:22:23,666 --> 00:22:26,166
[KIKUCHIYO] So wait,
this guy's name is Momotaro?

418
00:22:32,458 --> 00:22:34,333
[KAMBEI] I'm sorry
I had to involve you.

419
00:22:34,416 --> 00:22:36,333
[KIRARA] And it's
all because of us...

420
00:22:36,416 --> 00:22:37,875
It was a nice dream
I was having,

421
00:22:37,958 --> 00:22:40,125
but we all have to
wake up some time.

422
00:22:45,750 --> 00:22:48,000
[ENGINE ACCELERATING]

423
00:22:48,083 --> 00:22:49,500
We've got company.

424
00:22:55,833 --> 00:22:57,791
[KOMACHI]
Someone's up ahead, too.

425
00:22:59,166 --> 00:23:01,375
Shikimoribito.

426
00:23:05,375 --> 00:23:06,791
Ah...!

427
00:23:13,541 --> 00:23:18,500
♪ closing song ♪

428
00:25:22,291 --> 00:25:24,875
[KOMACHI] Dear Okara.
Today was a very good day!

429
00:25:24,958 --> 00:25:27,625
Even though everybody else said
that Kiku was gone for good,

430
00:25:27,708 --> 00:25:29,125
I just knew he'd be back...

431
00:25:29,208 --> 00:25:32,500
And he's better and stronger
and funnier than before!

432
00:25:32,583 --> 00:25:34,625
As if that weren't enough
excitement for one day,

433
00:25:34,708 --> 00:25:36,208
we met a new samurai.

434
00:25:36,291 --> 00:25:38,958
Well, Shichiroji's not
really a samurai, anymore.

435
00:25:39,041 --> 00:25:41,250
He works at a teahouse
in the Village of Respite,

436
00:25:41,333 --> 00:25:42,833
which is where they wash souls.

437
00:25:42,916 --> 00:25:45,625
His girlfriend, Yukino,
is so pretty and nice.

438
00:25:45,708 --> 00:25:47,416
I wanna be just like her!

439
00:25:47,500 --> 00:25:50,458
It's funny, most of our samurai
aren't samurai anymore.

440
00:25:50,541 --> 00:25:52,666
When we found him,
Heihachi was a wood-chopper

441
00:25:52,750 --> 00:25:54,583
and Gorobei is a
street performer.

442
00:25:54,666 --> 00:25:57,291
I guess since the war ended,
they had to find other jobs.

443
00:25:57,375 --> 00:25:59,875
If I had to get a job, I think
I'd like to be an empress.

444
00:25:59,958 --> 00:26:01,541
Or maybe a pirate!

445
00:26:01,625 --> 00:26:03,625
I don't know why Kambei
never took another job,

446
00:26:03,708 --> 00:26:04,875
but then again, 
I can't imagine him

447
00:26:04,958 --> 00:26:07,666
being anything but a
samurai... or a teacher.

448
00:26:07,750 --> 00:26:08,958
Oh, and I almost forgot,

449
00:26:09,041 --> 00:26:10,583
I learned some new
songs at the teahouse.

450
00:26:10,666 --> 00:26:13,458
I can't wait to
sing them for you!

451
00:26:13,541 --> 00:26:15,416
But I'm getting
kinda sleepy now.

452
00:26:15,500 --> 00:26:17,000
So bye bye...

